    <h1>CCPA (California Consumer Privacy Act)</h1>
    <p class="description">A California state privacy statute that gives residents four rights over their personal data: <strong>know, delete, correct, and opt out of sale</strong>. Effective since 2020 and enforced by the California Privacy Protection Agency.</p>
